```c
if (offsetof(struct INDEX_BUFFER, ihdr) + ib->ihdr.used > bytes) {
    err = -EINVAL;
    goto out;
}
```
This ensures that the index header doesn't exceed the allocated buffer size, preventing out-of-bounds access.

